{tier:0,icon:"🔐",name:"Public, Private & SerializeField",build:()=>`
<div class="lesson-header">
  <div class="tier-pill" style="background:rgba(96,165,250,0.1);color:#60a5fa">Tier 1 — C# Basics</div>
  <h1>🔐 Public, Private &amp; SerializeField</h1>
  <p>Access modifiers control who can read or change a variable. Getting this right is the difference between clean, safe code and a spaghetti mess.</p>
  <div class="badges"><span class="badge new">★ public</span><span class="badge new">★ private</span><span class="badge new">★ [SerializeField]</span><span class="badge new">★ protected</span><span class="badge new">★ properties</span></div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🧠 Access Modifiers at a Glance</h2>
  <table class="ctable">
    <tr><th>Modifier</th><th>Other scripts can read?</th><th>Other scripts can change?</th><th>Shows in Inspector?</th><th>Use for</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>public</code></td><td>✅ Yes</td><td>✅ Yes</td><td>✅ Yes</td><td>API — methods/data other objects NEED to access</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>private</code></td><td>❌ No</td><td>❌ No</td><td>❌ No</td><td>Internal data nobody else should touch</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>[SerializeField] private</code></td><td>❌ No</td><td>❌ No</td><td>✅ Yes</td><td><strong>Best practice</strong> — editable in Inspector, protected in code</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>protected</code></td><td>Subclasses only</td><td>Subclasses only</td><td>❌ No</td><td>Base class data subclasses need</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>public static</code></td><td>✅ Anywhere</td><td>✅ Anywhere</td><td>❌ No</td><td>Shared data (score, instance, constants)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>private readonly</code></td><td>❌ No</td><td>Set in constructor only</td><td>❌ No</td><td>Values set once and never changed</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>💻 Why Private is (Almost) Always Better</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm">// ✗ BAD — everything public = anyone can break anything</span>
<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">Player</span> : <span class="uk">MonoBehaviour</span>
{
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> health = <span class="num">100</span>;  <span class="cm">// any script can set health = -9999!</span>
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">float</span> speed = <span class="num">5f</span>;   <span class="cm">// any script can set speed = 0!</span>
}

<span class="cm">// ✓ GOOD — private with [SerializeField] = safe + Inspector-editable</span>
<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">Player</span> : <span class="uk">MonoBehaviour</span>
{
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">int</span>   maxHealth = <span class="num">100</span>;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">float</span> speed     = <span class="num">5f</span>;

    <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">int</span> currentHealth;   <span class="cm">// internal — no Inspector needed</span>

    <span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Start</span>() { currentHealth = maxHealth; }

    <span class="cm">// Controlled access — only reduce health through this method</span>
    <span class="kw">public void</span> <span class="fn">TakeDamage</span>(<span class="ty">int</span> amount)
    {
        currentHealth = <span class="uk">Mathf</span>.<span class="fn">Clamp</span>(currentHealth - amount, <span class="num">0</span>, maxHealth);
        <span class="kw">if</span> (currentHealth == <span class="num">0</span>) <span class="fn">Die</span>();
    }

    <span class="cm">// Read-only access from outside (nobody can SET health directly)</span>
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> Health => currentHealth;  <span class="cm">// get-only property</span>
}</pre>
  <div class="tip-box">💡 <strong>The rule:</strong> start everything as <code>private</code>. Only make something <code>public</code> when another script actively needs to call it. This prevents bugs where code accidentally modifies something it shouldn't.</div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🏗️ Properties — Get &amp; Set</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm">// A property looks like a field to callers but runs code behind the scenes</span>
<span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">int</span> health = <span class="num">100</span>;

<span class="cm">// Full property with validation</span>
<span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> Health
{
    <span class="kw">get</span> { <span class="kw">return</span> health; }
