}`,
  [
    "MovePosition() cannot use Vector3.forward",
    "speed should be private not public",
    "GetComponent<Rigidbody>() is called every FixedUpdate — it should be cached in Awake()",
    "Time.fixedDeltaTime should be Time.deltaTime"
  ],
  2,
  "GetComponent() is an expensive search that should never be called every frame. Cache it in Awake(): private Rigidbody rb; then void Awake() { rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>(); }"
)}

${CHALLENGES([
  "Write a complete MonoBehaviour script with Awake, Start, Update, and OnDestroy — each printing a message so you can see the order in the console.",
  "Create a script that counts the total number of Update() calls since the game started and prints it every second.",
  "Write a script that caches the Rigidbody, Animator, and AudioSource in Awake — with null checks for each.",
  "Use [SerializeField] to expose speed, jumpForce, and maxHealth in the Inspector while keeping them private in code.",
  "Write a simple timer in Update() using Time.deltaTime that fires a Debug.Log every 3 seconds.",
])}
`},,

{tier:3,icon:"🔦",name:"Raycasting",build:()=>`
<div class="lesson-header">
  <div class="tier-pill" style="background:rgba(52,211,153,0.1);color:#34d399">Tier 4 — Unity Core</div>
  <h1>🔦 Raycasting</h1>
  <p>A raycast fires an invisible ray from a point in a direction and tells you what it hits. Used for shooting, line-of-sight, ground detection, and more.</p>
