{tier:3,icon:"🕹️",name:"Input & Movement",build:()=>`
<div class="lesson-header">
  <div class="tier-pill" style="background:rgba(52,211,153,0.1);color:#34d399">Tier 4 — Unity Core</div>
  <h1>🕹️ Input &amp; Player Movement</h1>
  <p>Respond to keyboard, mouse and controller input. Move objects using Transform or Rigidbody depending on whether you need physics.</p>
  <div class="badges"><span class="badge unity">★ Input.GetKey</span><span class="badge unity">★ Input.GetAxis</span><span class="badge unity">★ Transform.Translate</span><span class="badge unity">★ Rigidbody.MovePosition</span><span class="badge unity">★ Time.deltaTime</span></div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>⌨️ Input Methods Reference</h2>
  <table class="ctable">
    <tr><th>Method</th><th>Returns</th><th>True when</th><th>Best use</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetKey(KeyCode.W)</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Key held down</td><td>Continuous movement/actions</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetKeyDown(KeyCode.Space)</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Key pressed THIS frame</td><td>Jump, shoot, interact</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetKeyUp(KeyCode.Space)</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Key released THIS frame</td><td>Charge-release mechanics</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetAxis("Horizontal")</code></td><td>float -1 to 1</td><td>Always</td><td>Smooth movement, analogue input</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetAxisRaw("Horizontal")</code></td><td>-1, 0, or 1</td><td>Always</td><td>Crisp digital movement</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.GetMouseButtonDown(0)</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Left mouse clicked this frame</td><td>Shooting, UI clicks</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>Input.mousePosition</code></td><td>Vector3</td><td>Always</td><td>Aim direction, cursor UI</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>💻 Movement Patterns</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm">// ── Transform movement (no physics collisions) ──</span>
<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Update</span>()
{
    <span class="ty">float</span> h = <span class="uk">Input</span>.<span class="fn">GetAxis</span>(<span class="str">"Horizontal"</span>);
    <span class="ty">float</span> v = <span class="uk">Input</span>.<span class="fn">GetAxis</span>(<span class="str">"Vertical"</span>);

    <span class="cm">// Time.deltaTime makes movement frame-rate independent!</span>
    transform.<span class="fn">Translate</span>(h * speed * <span class="uk">Time</span>.deltaTime,
                         <span class="num">0</span>,
                         v * speed * <span class="uk">Time</span>.deltaTime);
}

<span class="cm">// ── Rigidbody movement (respects physics) ──</span>
<span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">Rigidbody</span> rb;

<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Awake</span>() { rb = <span class="fn">GetComponent</span>&lt;<span class="ty">Rigidbody</span>&gt;(); }

<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">FixedUpdate</span>()    <span class="cm">// ← physics goes in FixedUpdate!</span>
{
    <span class="ty">float</span> h = <span class="uk">Input</span>.<span class="fn">GetAxis</span>(<span class="str">"Horizontal"</span>);
    <span class="ty">float</span> v = <span class="uk">Input</span>.<span class="fn">GetAxis</span>(<span class="str">"Vertical"</span>);
    <span class="ty">Vector3</span> move = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="ty">Vector3</span>(h, <span class="num">0</span>, v).normalized;
    rb.<span class="fn">MovePosition</span>(rb.position + move * speed * <span class="uk">Time</span>.fixedDeltaTime);
}

<span class="cm">// ── Jump (single press, with ground check) ──</span>
<span class="ty">bool</span> isGrounded = <span class="kw">true</span>;

<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Update</span>()
{
    <span class="kw">if</span> (<span class="uk">Input</span>.<span class="fn">GetKeyDown</span>(<span class="uk">KeyCode</span>.Space) && isGrounded)
    {
        rb.<span class="fn">AddForce</span>(<span class="ty">Vector3</span>.up * jumpForce, <span class="uk">ForceMode</span>.Impulse);
        isGrounded = <span class="kw">false</span>;
    }
}</pre>

  <div class="note-box">⚠️ <strong>Always multiply by Time.deltaTime!</strong> Without it, movement speed depends on frame rate — faster on a 144fps monitor, slower on 30fps. With deltaTime, it's consistent at all frame rates.</div>
  <div class="unity-box">🎮 <strong>GetKey vs GetKeyDown:</strong> For jump, ALWAYS use GetKeyDown. GetKey is true every frame the key is held — that would make the player jump 60 times per second!</div>
</div>

${Q([
  {q:"Why multiply movement by <code>Time.deltaTime</code>?",opts:["To make the player move faster","To make movement frame-rate independent","To synchronise with the physics engine","It converts from pixels to units"],ans:1,explain:"Time.deltaTime is the time in seconds since the last frame. Multiplying by it means the player moves X units per second regardless of frame rate — smooth on all machines."},
  {q:"For jump, you should use which input method?",opts:["Input.GetKey(KeyCode.Space)","Input.GetKeyDown(KeyCode.Space)","Input.GetAxis('Jump')","Input.GetKeyUp(KeyCode.Space)"],ans:1,explain:"GetKeyDown is only true on the single frame the key is first pressed. GetKey is true every frame the key is held — this would fire jump repeatedly. GetKeyDown is correct for single-press actions."},
  {q:"Where should Rigidbody movement code go?",opts:["Awake()","Start()","Update()","FixedUpdate()"],ans:3,explain:"All Rigidbody physics operations (AddForce, MovePosition, velocity) belong in FixedUpdate(). It runs on a fixed timestep that's in sync with Unity's physics engine."},
  {q:"<code>Input.GetAxis('Horizontal')</code> returns what type of value?",opts:["int (-1 or 1)","bool","float (-1.0 to 1.0)","string"],ans:2,explain:"GetAxis returns a float between -1.0 and 1.0. It also smoothly interpolates — pressing left doesn't instantly snap to -1, it eases there. Use GetAxisRaw for instant snapping."},
  {q:"What does <code>.normalized</code> do to a Vector3?",opts:["Makes all components 1","Sets the length to 1 while keeping direction","Rounds to nearest integer","Multiplies by Time.deltaTime"],ans:1,explain:"normalized returns a vector with the same direction but a length (magnitude) of exactly 1. Without it, diagonal movement (forward+right) is sqrt(2) = 1.41x faster than straight movement."},
  {q:"Player is sliding on ice (moving without input). Which Rigidbody setting fixes this?",opts:["Increase mass","Increase Angular Drag","Increase Linear Drag","Set Is Kinematic = true"],ans:2,explain:"Drag (linear drag) slows the Rigidbody's velocity over time, simulating friction/air resistance. Increasing it stops the sliding. Angular Drag only affects rotation."},
])}

${FIB("Complete the 2D platformer movement:",
`<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Update</span>()
{
    <span class="ty">float</span> h = <span class="uk">Input</span>.${blank('GetAxis',8)}(<span class="str">"Horizontal"</span>);
    transform.${blank('Translate',10)}(h * speed * <span class="uk">Time</span>.${blank('deltaTime',10)}, <span class="num">0</span>, <span class="num">0</span>);

    <span class="kw">if</span> (<span class="uk">Input</span>.${blank('GetKeyDown',11)}(${blank('KeyCode',8)}.Space) && isGrounded)
    {
        rb.${blank('AddForce',10)}(<span class="ty">Vector3</span>.up * jumpForce, <span class="uk">ForceMode</span>.Impulse);
        isGrounded = <span class="kw">false</span>;
    }
}`,
['GetAxis','Translate','deltaTime','GetKeyDown','KeyCode','AddForce'])}

${BUG(
  "This movement code works but the player moves faster diagonally than straight. Find the bug:",
  `void Update()
{
    float h = Input.GetAxis("Horizontal");
    float v = Input.GetAxis("Vertical");
    Vector3 direction = new Vector3(h, 0, v);
    transform.Translate(direction * speed * Time.deltaTime);
}`,
  [
    "GetAxis should be GetAxisRaw",
    "The Vector3 direction should be normalized — without it, diagonal movement is ~41% faster",
    "transform.Translate should be rb.MovePosition",
    "Time.deltaTime should be Time.fixedDeltaTime"
  ],
  1,
  "When h=1 and v=1 (diagonal), the Vector3(1,0,1) has a magnitude of sqrt(2) ≈ 1.41, making diagonal movement 41% faster. Fix: direction = new Vector3(h, 0, v).normalized;"
)}

${CHALLENGES([
  "Write a movement script that restricts the player to a 10x10 unit area using Mathf.Clamp.",
  "Add a sprint mechanic: hold Left Shift to double movement speed.",
  "Make an object rotate to face the mouse cursor position using Quaternion.LookRotation.",
