])}
`},,

{tier:3,icon:"💥",name:"Collisions & Triggers",build:()=>`
<div class="lesson-header">
  <div class="tier-pill" style="background:rgba(52,211,153,0.1);color:#34d399">Tier 4 — Unity Core</div>
  <h1>💥 Collisions &amp; Triggers</h1>
  <p>Detect when objects touch, overlap, or enter zones. Almost every game mechanic involves collision detection.</p>
  <div class="badges"><span class="badge unity">★ OnCollisionEnter</span><span class="badge unity">★ OnTriggerEnter</span><span class="badge unity">★ CompareTag</span><span class="badge unity">★ GetComponent from other</span><span class="badge unity">★ layers</span></div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🔍 Collision vs Trigger — Key Differences</h2>
  <table class="ctable">
    <tr><th></th><th>Collision (solid)</th><th>Trigger (zone)</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Is Trigger setting</strong></td><td>OFF</td><td>ON</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Physical response</strong></td><td>Yes — objects push/bounce</td><td>No — objects pass through</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Use for</strong></td><td>Walls, floors, platforms</td><td>Pickups, hazard zones, doors</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Enter callback</strong></td><td><code>OnCollisionEnter(Collision col)</code></td><td><code>OnTriggerEnter(Collider other)</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Stay callback</strong></td><td><code>OnCollisionStay(Collision col)</code></td><td><code>OnTriggerStay(Collider other)</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Exit callback</strong></td><td><code>OnCollisionExit(Collision col)</code></td><td><code>OnTriggerExit(Collider other)</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Requires Rigidbody?</strong></td><td>At least one object needs one</td><td>At least one object needs one</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>💻 Collision Code Patterns</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm">// ── Collision — physical contact ──</span>
<span class="kw">private void</span> <span class="fn">OnCollisionEnter</span>(<span class="ty">Collision</span> collision)
{
    <span class="cm">// Always use CompareTag — faster than .tag ==</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> (collision.gameObject.<span class="fn">CompareTag</span>(<span class="str">"Enemy"</span>))
    {
        <span class="fn">TakeDamage</span>(<span class="num">10</span>);
    }

    <span class="cm">// Get a component from the object we collided with</span>
    <span class="ty">EnemyController</span> enemy = collision.gameObject.<span class="fn">GetComponent</span>&lt;<span class="ty">EnemyController</span>&gt;();
    <span class="kw">if</span> (enemy != <span class="kw">null</span>)
    {
        health -= enemy.damage;
    }
}

<span class="cm">// ── Trigger — overlap zone ──</span>
<span class="kw">private void</span> <span class="fn">OnTriggerEnter</span>(<span class="ty">Collider</span> other)
{
    <span class="kw">if</span> (other.<span class="fn">CompareTag</span>(<span class="str">"Coin"</span>))
    {
        score += <span class="num">10</span>;
        <span class="uk">Destroy</span>(other.gameObject);
    }

    <span class="kw">if</span> (other.<span class="fn">CompareTag</span>(<span class="str">"DeathZone"</span>))
    {
        <span class="fn">Die</span>();
    }

    <span class="kw">if</span> (other.<span class="fn">CompareTag</span>(<span class="str">"Finish"</span>))
    {
        <span class="uk">Debug</span>.<span class="fn">Log</span>(<span class="str">"Level complete!"</span>);
        <span class="fn">LoadNextLevel</span>();
    }
}</pre>

  <div class="unity-box">🎮 <strong>Setup checklist:</strong><br>
  ✓ Both objects have a Collider<br>
  ✓ At least one object has a Rigidbody<br>
  ✓ If using trigger: Is Trigger = ON on the zone's Collider<br>
  ✓ Tags set correctly in the Inspector<br>
  ✓ Layer Collision Matrix set if needed (Physics settings)</div>
</div>

${Q([
  {q:"What is the key difference between a Collision and a Trigger in Unity?",opts:["No difference","Collision provides physical response; Trigger lets objects pass through","Trigger is faster","Collision only works in 3D"],ans:1,explain:"Collision = physical impact (objects stop/bounce). Trigger = objects pass through but you get a callback. Set Is Trigger ON in the Collider component to make it a trigger."},
  {q:"Why use <code>CompareTag(\"Enemy\")</code> instead of <code>gameObject.tag == \"Enemy\"</code>?",opts:["They are identical","CompareTag is faster and avoids garbage allocation","CompareTag works offline","gameObject.tag is deprecated"],ans:1,explain:"CompareTag() is optimised for performance. Using tag == creates a new string object which adds to garbage collection pressure. Unity recommends CompareTag always."},
  {q:"The script is on a coin. Player walks into it. Which callback should you use to detect this?",opts:["OnCollisionEnter","OnTriggerEnter","OnCollisionStay","Update"],ans:1,explain:"For a pickup (coin), you want a trigger zone that doesn't stop the player. Set Is Trigger = ON and use OnTriggerEnter. The Collider parameter gives you access to the entering object."},
  {q:"You get a component from the colliding object with <code>GetComponent&lt;EnemyAI&gt;()</code>. What should you check before using it?",opts:["Nothing — it always works","That the object has the right tag","That the result is not null","That the Rigidbody is Kinematic"],ans:2,explain:"GetComponent returns null if the component doesn't exist on that object. Always check: if (component != null) before using it, or your game will throw a NullReferenceException."},
  {q:"Which parameter type does OnTriggerEnter use?",opts:["Collision","Collider","GameObject","RigidBody"],ans:1,explain:"OnTriggerEnter(Collider other) — the parameter is a Collider. OnCollisionEnter(Collision collision) — that uses Collision (capital, different type). Don't mix them up!"},
  {q:"For collision callbacks to fire, what must at least ONE of the two objects have?",opts:["A Trigger","A Tag","A Rigidbody","A Script"],ans:2,explain:"At least one of the two colliding objects needs a Rigidbody for Unity's physics system to generate collision events. Static objects (no Rigidbody) colliding with each other generate no callbacks."},
])}

${FIB("Complete the coin pickup script:",
`<span class="kw">private void</span> ${blank('OnTriggerEnter',14)}(<span class="ty">Collider</span> other)
{
    <span class="kw">if</span> (other.${blank('CompareTag',11)}(<span class="str">"Player"</span>))
    {
        <span class="cm">// Add score to the player's script</span>
        <span class="ty">PlayerScore</span> ps = other.${blank('GetComponent',13)}&lt;<span class="ty">PlayerScore</span>&gt;();
        <span class="kw">if</span> (ps ${blank('!=',3)} <span class="kw">null</span>)
        {
            ps.${blank('AddScore',9)}(<span class="num">10</span>);
        }
        <span class="uk">Destroy</span>(${blank('gameObject',11)});
    }
}`,
['OnTriggerEnter','CompareTag','GetComponent','!=','AddScore','gameObject'])}

${BUG(
  "This damage script should reduce health when the player hits an enemy. It compiles but never runs:",
  `public class PlayerHealth : MonoBehaviour
{
    public int health = 100;

    private void OnTriggerEnter(Collider other)
    {
        if (other.CompareTag("Enemy"))
        {
            health -= 10;
        }
    }
}`,
  [
    "CompareTag is spelled wrong",
    "health should be a float not int",
    "The player's Collider probably doesn't have Is Trigger checked — so OnCollisionEnter should be used instead, OR Is Trigger needs to be enabled",
    "health -= 10 should be health = health - 10"
  ],
  2,
  "OnTriggerEnter only fires when the Collider has 'Is Trigger' checked in the Inspector. If the player is a solid physical object, you should either: (1) check Is Trigger on the enemy's hitbox, or (2) use OnCollisionEnter instead. Also ensure a Rigidbody is present."
)}

${CHALLENGES([
  "Create a hazard zone trigger: when the player enters, reduce health by 5 every second (hint: use OnTriggerStay with Time.deltaTime).",
  "Build a checkpoint system: trigger zones that save a respawn position when entered.",
  "Create a 'detect nearby enemies' trigger: a sphere collider on the player that logs all enemies that enter its range.",
  "Build a one-way platform: a collision that only blocks the player from below (hint: check collision.contacts[0].normal).",
  "Create a door trigger: when the player enters with a key item, the door opens (set a bool on enter, close on exit).",
])}
`},,

