{tier:7,icon:"🏆",name:"Capstone: Coin Collector",build:()=>`
<div class="lesson-header">
  <div class="tier-pill" style="background:rgba(251,191,36,0.1);color:#fbbf24">Tier 8 — Capstone Project</div>
  <h1>🏆 Capstone Project: Coin Collector</h1>
  <p>Build a complete, playable 3D game from scratch. You will write every script yourself using the concepts from every lesson in this curriculum.</p>
  <div class="badges">
    <span class="badge new">★ Full Game</span><span class="badge rep">★ MonoBehaviour</span><span class="badge rep">★ Rigidbody</span>
    <span class="badge rep">★ Triggers</span><span class="badge rep">★ UI</span><span class="badge rep">★ Coroutines</span>
    <span class="badge rep">★ Interfaces</span><span class="badge rep">★ SceneManager</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🎮 What You're Building</h2>
  <table class="ctable">
    <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Concept Used</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Player moves with WASD, jumps with Space</td><td>Input.GetAxis, Rigidbody, FixedUpdate</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Single jump only (no double-jump)</td><td>Raycast ground check</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Coins spin — collected on touch</td><td>OnTriggerEnter, Destroy, Coroutine</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Enemy patrols between waypoints</td><td>Vector3.MoveTowards, arrays</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Getting hit costs a life + respawns player</td><td>IDamageable interface</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Score and Lives shown on screen</td><td>TextMeshPro, GameManager singleton</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Win when all coins collected</td><td>SceneManager</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Lose when lives hit 0</td><td>Time.timeScale</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="unity-box">🎮 <strong>Before you start:</strong> Create a new <strong>3D Core</strong> Unity project. Make these folders in your Project panel: <code>Scripts/</code> <code>Materials/</code> <code>Prefabs/</code></div>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🎨 What is a Material?</h2>
  <p>A <strong>Material</strong> tells Unity how the surface of an object looks — its colour, shininess, and texture. Without a Material, everything is a flat white/grey.</p>
  <pre><span class="cm">// HOW TO CREATE A MATERIAL:
// 1. In the Project panel, right-click your Materials/ folder
// 2. Create → Material
// 3. Name it (e.g. "GreenFloor", "YellowCoin", "RedEnemy")
// 4. In the Inspector, click the Albedo colour box and pick a colour
// 5. Drag the Material from Project onto a GameObject in the Scene
//    — or drag it onto the object in the Hierarchy

// You need one material per colour you want to use.
// You can reuse the same material on many objects.</span></pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>📐 Phase 1 — Build the Scene</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm">// ── STEP 1: Floor ────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hierarchy → right-click → 3D Object → Plane
// Name it "Floor" | Scale: (5, 1, 5)
// Create a green Material and drag it onto the Floor</span>

<span class="cm">// ── STEP 2: Walls (keeps player from falling off) ─────────────────
// Create 4 Cubes: Wall_N, Wall_S, Wall_E, Wall_W
// North/South walls: Scale (50, 3, 1)
// East/West walls:   Scale (1, 3, 50)
// Position around the floor edges</span>

<span class="cm">// ── STEP 3: Player ───────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hierarchy → 3D Object → Capsule  →  name "Player"
// Position: (0, 1, 0)
// Add Component → Rigidbody
//   In Rigidbody: expand Constraints → Freeze Rotation X, Y, Z
//   (stops it from tipping over when it moves)
// Tag: "Player"  (top of Inspector → Tag dropdown → Add Tag → type Player → Save)
// Layer: "Ground" — we'll use this for the jump check
//   Top of Inspector → Layer → Add Layer → type "Ground" → assign Floor to Ground layer</span>

<span class="cm">// ── STEP 4: Coin ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hierarchy → 3D Object → Cylinder  →  name "Coin"
// Scale: (0.5, 0.1, 0.5)  ←  flat disc shape
// Create a yellow Material and apply it
// The Capsule Collider is added automatically — click it in the Inspector
//   Check the "Is Trigger" box  ←  makes it a zone, not a solid wall
// Tag: "Coin"
// Place several around the scene (Ctrl+D to duplicate)</span>

<span class="cm">// ── STEP 5: Enemy ────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Hierarchy → 3D Object → Cube  →  name "Enemy"
// Create a red Material and apply it
// Add Component → Rigidbody → check "Is Kinematic"
//   (Kinematic = we move it manually, not by physics forces)</span>

<span class="cm">// ── STEP 6: Waypoints ────────────────────────────────────────────
// Create 4 empty GameObjects (right-click → Create Empty)
// Name: Waypoint1, Waypoint2, Waypoint3, Waypoint4
// Place them at different corners of the scene
// In Hierarchy, drag all 4 onto a new empty parent called "Waypoints"</span></pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>🔵 What is a Layer Mask?</h2>
  <p>Layers let you group objects so raycasts and physics can <em>selectively</em> interact with only certain groups. A <strong>Layer Mask</strong> is a filter — "only detect objects on this layer".</p>
  <pre><span class="cm">// WHY WE NEED IT:
// The ground-check raycast fires downward from the player.
// Without a Layer Mask it might hit the player's own collider
// or coins and think the player is "grounded" mid-air.
// By pointing it at only the "Ground" layer we get a reliable result.

// HOW TO SET UP THE GROUND LAYER:
// 1. Select your Floor object in the Hierarchy
// 2. Top of Inspector → Layer dropdown → Add Layer
// 3. Type "Ground" in one of the empty User Layer slots → hit Enter
// 4. Select Floor again → Layer → Ground  (assign it)
// 5. Do the same for your Walls
// 6. In the PlayerController component in the Inspector,
//    the "Ground Mask" field will appear — set it to "Ground"</span></pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>📝 Phase 2 — IDamageable.cs</h2>
  <p>Create this first. It's a plain C# file — <strong>right-click Scripts/ → Create → MonoBehaviour Script → name it IDamageable</strong>, then replace all contents with:</p>
  <pre><span class="cm">// Scripts/IDamageable.cs</span>
<span class="kw">public interface</span> <span class="ty">IDamageable</span>
{
    <span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">TakeDamage</span>(<span class="ty">int</span> amount);
    <span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Die</span>();
}
<span class="cm">// This file has NO MonoBehaviour — it's just the interface contract.
// Delete everything Unity generated and paste the above.</span></pre>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2>📝 Phase 3 — GameManager.cs</h2>
  <p><strong>Create → MonoBehaviour Script → "GameManager".</strong> Attach it to a new empty GameObject also called "GameManager".</p>
  <pre><span class="cm">// Scripts/GameManager.cs</span>
<span class="kw">using</span> UnityEngine;
<span class="kw">using</span> UnityEngine.SceneManagement;
<span class="kw">using</span> TMPro;

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="ty">GameManager</span> : <span class="uk">MonoBehaviour</span>
{
    <span class="cm">// ── Singleton ──────────────────────────────────────────────────</span>
    <span class="kw">public static</span> <span class="ty">GameManager</span> Instance { <span class="kw">get</span>; <span class="kw">private set</span>; }

    <span class="cm">// ── Game state (instance variables — no static) ────────────────</span>
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> Score      { <span class="kw">get</span>; <span class="kw">private set</span>; }
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> Lives      { <span class="kw">get</span>; <span class="kw">private set</span>; } = <span class="num">3</span>;
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="ty">int</span> CoinsLeft  { <span class="kw">get</span>; <span class="kw">private set</span>; }

    <span class="cm">// ── UI — drag these in from the Inspector ──────────────────────</span>
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">TextMeshProUGUI</span> scoreText;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">TextMeshProUGUI</span> livesText;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">TextMeshProUGUI</span> coinsText;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">GameObject</span>       winPanel;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">GameObject</span>       losePanel;
    [<span class="uk">SerializeField</span>] <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="ty">TextMeshProUGUI</span> finalScoreText;

    <span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">Awake</span>()
    {
        <span class="kw">if</span> (Instance == <span class="kw">null</span>) Instance = <span class="kw">this</span>;
        <span class="kw">else</span> { <span class="uk">Destroy</span>(gameObject); <span class="kw">return</span>; }

        CoinsLeft = FindObjectsOfType&lt;<span class="ty">CoinPickup</span>&gt;().Length;
        <span class="fn">UpdateUI</span>();
    }

    <span class="kw">public void</span> <span class="fn">CoinCollected</span>()
    {
        Score++;
        CoinsLeft--;
        <span class="fn">UpdateUI</span>();
        <span class="kw">if</span> (CoinsLeft &lt;= <span class="num">0</span>) <span class="fn">Win</span>();
    }

    <span class="kw">public void</span> <span class="fn">PlayerDied</span>()
    {
        Lives--;
        <span class="fn">UpdateUI</span>();
        <span class="kw">if</span> (Lives &lt;= <span class="num">0</span>) <span class="fn">Lose</span>();
    }

    <span class="kw">private void</span> <span class="fn">UpdateUI</span>()
    {
        <span class="kw">if</span> (scoreText)  scoreText.text  = <span class="str">$"Coins: {Score}"</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span> (livesText)  livesText.text  = <span class="str">$"Lives: {Lives}"</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span> (coinsText)  coinsText.text  = <span class="str">$"{CoinsLeft} left"</span>;
    }

    <span class="kw">private void</span> <span class="fn">Win</span>()
    {
        <span class="uk">Time</span>.timeScale = <span class="num">0f</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span> (winPanel)       winPanel.<span class="fn">SetActive</span>(<span class="kw">true</span>);
        <span class="kw">if</span> (finalScoreText) finalScoreText.text = <span class="str">$"You collected all {Score} coins!"</span>;
    }

    <span class="kw">private void</span> <span class="fn">Lose</span>()
    {
        <span class="uk">Time</span>.timeScale = <span class="num">0f</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span> (losePanel)      losePanel.<span class="fn">SetActive</span>(<span class="kw">true</span>);
        <span class="kw">if</span> (finalScoreText) finalScoreText.text = <span class="str">$"You got {Score} coins."</span>;
    }

    <span class="kw">public void</span> <span class="fn">RestartGame</span>()
    {
        <span class="uk">Time</span>.timeScale = <span class="num">1f</span>;
        <span class="uk">SceneManager</span>.<span class="fn">LoadScene</span>(<span class="uk">SceneManager</span>.GetActiveScene().buildIndex);
    }
}</pre>
